Пример 1¶

import plotly
import plotly.plotly as py
import plotly.graph_objs as go

import pandas as pd
plotly.offline.init_notebook_mode(connected=True)

# Read data from a csv
z_data = pd.read_csv('https://raw.githubusercontent.com/plotly/datasets/master/api_docs/mt_bruno_elevation.csv')

data = [
    go.Surface(
        z=z_data.as_matrix()
    )
]
layout = go.Layout(
    title='Mt Bruno Elevation',
    autosize=False,
    width=500,
    height=500,
    margin=dict(
        l=65,
        r=50,
        b=65,
        t=90
    )
)
fig = go.Figure(data=data, layout=layout)
plotly.offline.iplot(fig, filename='elevations-3d-surface')

import plotly
import plotly.plotly as py
from plotly.graph_objs import *
import plotly.graph_objs as go

import numpy as np
plotly.offline.init_notebook_mode(connected=True)

t = np.linspace(0, np.pi, 240)
tGrid, sGrid = np.meshgrid(s, t)

r = 1  # r = 2 + sin(7s+5t)
x = r * np.sin(tGrid)  # x = r*cos(s)*sin(t)
y = r * np.cos(tGrid)  # y = r*sin(s)*sin(t)
z = 0                 # z = r*cos(t)

surface = Surface(x=x, y=y, z=z)
data = Data([surface])

x1 = np.linspace(-2,2)
x2 = np.linspace(-2,2)
f = np.zeros((len(x1), len(x2)))

for i in range(len(x1)):
    for j in range(len(x2)):
        f[i][j] = x1[i]+ x2[j]
        
# xx, yy = np.mgrid[:200, :200]/200
# circle = (xx) ** 2 + (yy) ** 2

target_function = go.Surface(x = x1, y = x2, z=f)
constraint = go.Surface(x=0, y=0, z=0)

data_ = [target_function, constraint]



layout = Layout(
    title=' 1',
    scene=Scene(
        xaxis=XAxis(
            gridcolor='rgb(255, 255, 255)',
            zerolinecolor='rgb(255, 255, 255)',
            showbackground=True,
            backgroundcolor='rgb(230, 230,230)'
        ),
        yaxis=YAxis(
            gridcolor='rgb(255, 255, 255)',
            zerolinecolor='rgb(255, 255, 255)',
            showbackground=True,
            backgroundcolor='rgb(230, 230,230)'
        ),
        zaxis=ZAxis(
            gridcolor='rgb(255, 255, 255)',
            zerolinecolor='rgb(255, 255, 255)',
            showbackground=True,
            backgroundcolor='rgb(230, 230,230)'
        )
    )
)

fig = Figure(data=data_, layout=layout)
plotly.offline.iplot(fig, filename='jupyter/parametric_plot')

import plotly.plotly as py
import plotly.graph_objs as go
plotly.offline.init_notebook_mode(connected=True)

import numpy as np


s = np.linspace(0, 2 * np.pi, 240)
t = np.linspace(0, 2*np.pi, 240)
st, t = np.meshgrid(s, t)

r =  np.meshgrid(np.linspace(0,1,240), np.linspace(0,1,240))[0]
x = r * np.cos(t)# * np.sin(tGrid)  # x = r*cos(s)*sin(t)
y = r *np.sin(t)# * np.sin(tGrid)  # y = r*sin(s)*sin(t)
z = np.zeros((240,240))
surface = go.Surface(x=x, y=y, z=z)

x1 = np.linspace(-2,2)
x2 = np.linspace(-2,2)
f = np.zeros((len(x1), len(x2)))

for i in range(len(x1)):
    for j in range(len(x2)):
        f[i][j] = x1[i]+ x2[j]
        
# xx, yy = np.mgrid[:200, :200]/200
# circle = (xx) ** 2 + (yy) ** 2

target_function = go.Surface(x = x1, y = x2, z=f)

data = [surface, target_function]

layout = go.Layout(
    title='Parametric Plot',
    scene=dict(
        xaxis=dict(
            gridcolor='rgb(255, 255, 255)',
            zerolinecolor='rgb(255, 255, 255)',
            showbackground=True,
            backgroundcolor='rgb(230, 230,230)'
        ),
        yaxis=dict(
            gridcolor='rgb(255, 255, 255)',
            zerolinecolor='rgb(255, 255, 255)',
            showbackground=True,
            backgroundcolor='rgb(230, 230,230)'
        ),
        zaxis=dict(
            gridcolor='rgb(255, 255, 255)',
            zerolinecolor='rgb(255, 255, 255)',
            showbackground=True,
            backgroundcolor='rgb(230, 230,230)'
        )
    )
)

fig = go.Figure(data=data, layout=layout)
plotly.offline.iplot(fig, filename='jupyter/parametric_plot')
